y:Ace of Base]]\n[[Category:Pop music group discographies]]\n[[Category:Discographies of Swedish artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist          = [[Ace of Base]]\n|Image           = Ace OF Base Vantaa Finlandia 2-10-2008.JPG\n|Caption         = Ace of Base in 2008\n|Studio          = 5\n|Compilation     = 9\n|EP              = 2\n|Video           = \n|Singles         = 26\n|Music videos    = 24\n|B-sides         = \n|Soundtrack      = \n}}\nThis is the discography of [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[pop music|pop]] group [[Ace of Base]]. The group is the third best-selling group from Sweden after [[ABBA]] and [[Roxette]] with an estimated of over 30 million albums and 15 million singles sold worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a169980/michael-jackson-a-fan-of-ace-of-base.html|title= Michael Jackson 'a fan of Ace Of Base'|first=David|last=Balls|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]|date=August 10, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playgroundmusic.se/artister/ace-of-base/ |title=Ace Of Base - Officiell sida f\u00f6r Ace Of Base |publisher=Playgroundmusic.se |accessdate=20 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525200256/http://www.playgroundmusic.se/artister/ace-of-base/ |archivedate=25 May 2014 }}</ref> This is a list with all of their albums and singles released, along with highest chart positions reached in major territories. Extended chart information, artwork and track listings can be found on individual pages. To date, they have released five studio albums and twenty-eight singles.\n\n==Albums==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\" | Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11em;\" | [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]]\n|-\n!style=\"width