lop\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Never Gonna Say I'm Sorry\" (Morph version)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Richard Heslop\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Never Gonna Say I'm Sorry\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Richard Heslop\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" rowspan=\"1\"|1996\n|align=\"left\"|\"Lucky Love\" (US version)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" rowspan=\"6\"|1998\n|align=\"left\"|\"Life Is a Flower\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Cruel Summer\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Nigel Dick]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Cruel Summer\" (US version)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Nigel Dick\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Cruel Summer\" (French version featuring Alliage)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Always Have Always Will\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|\"Travel to Romantis\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Andy Neumann\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|1999\n|align=\"left\"|\"C'est la Vie (Always 21)\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Patric Ullaeus\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2002\n|align=\"left\"|\"Beautiful Morning\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Daniel Borjesson\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2003\n|align=\"left\"|\"Unspeakable\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Daniel Borjesson\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2008\n|align=\"left\"|\"Wheel of Fortune 2009\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2010\n|align=\"left\"|\"All for You\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Patric Ullaeus\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|2015\n|align=\"left\"|\"Would You Believe\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|Trace Adam\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{refbegin|1}}\n#{{note|1}} \"Never Gonna Say I'm Sorry\" peaked at number 16 on the [[Dutch Top 40]] [[:nl:Tipparade|Tipparade]], which ranks the top 30 songs that have not yet entered the main Dutch Top 40 chart. \n#{{note|1}} \"Cruel Summer\" peaked at number 6 on the [[:nl:Tipparade|Tipparade]], which ranks the top 30 songs that have not yet entered the main Dutch Top 40 chart.\n{{refend|1}}